//theory
getElementId(): returns the element by having given the id value.targets a single element 

getElementbyClassName() : returns all the elements having the same class name
HTML Collection object 

Collection object:
An HTML collection is array like list of HTML elements
Length property provides the size of the html elements

QuerySelector
Queryselector:used to select HTML element by its className ,tagname;it selects only the first element

Can be used to select the elements by its tagname or classname.It returns  a node list which is an array like object

Manipulate Elements:
To create a HTML element:
–createElement()
–document.createElement()
–This method takes an HTML  element tag name as a string parameter.
We can create multiple elements by using array






